        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 4:04PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 404 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ohio City, or near Van Wert, moving northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monticello, Glenmore, Monmouth, Wren, Decatur, Dull, Abanaka,
Jonestown, Middlebury, Rivare, Venedocia, Schumm, Elgin, Willshire,
Pleasant Mills, Ohio City, Van Wert, and Monroe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
